<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>This element models the gravity of a massive object whose center of gravity is far away (and thus the gravitational pull is effectively constant across the scene). To model the gravity of an object near or inside the scene, use <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-attractor3d.xml">Attractor3D</db:link>.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="property-documentation">
<db:title>Property Documentation</db:title>
<db:section xml:id="direction-prop">
<db:title>direction : vector3d</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>vector3d</db:type>
<db:varname>direction</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the direction the gravity will affect toward. Values will be automatically normalized to a unit vector.</db:para>
<db:para>The default value is <db:code>(0.0, -1.0, 0.0)</db:code> (downwards).</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="magnitude-prop">
<db:title>magnitude : real</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>real</db:type>
<db:varname>magnitude</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the magnitude in position change per second. Negative magnitude accelerates the opposite way from the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-gravity3d.xml#direction-prop">direction</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:para>The default value is <db:code>100.0</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
</db:section>
